annotationA: Phosphoserine phosphatase; Catalyzes the last step in the biosynthesis of serine from carbohydrates. The reaction mechanism proceeds via the formation of a phosphoryl-enzyme intermediates (By similarity)
annotationB: Cystathionine beta-synthase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: determination of adult lifespan; cysteine biosynthetic process from serine; response to endoplasmic reticulum stress; cysteine biosynthetic process via cystathionine
